@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{forge-extras.el} extends @samp{forge}, the Emacs package that integrates Git
forges (GitHub, GitLab, and others) into Magit.  While @samp{forge} handles
the fundamentals---pulling topics, viewing issues and pull requests,
posting comments---@samp{forge-extras.el} adds higher-level workflows on top
of that foundation.

The package addresses two broad areas:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Everyday issue and notification management.}  Commands for toggling
issue state, navigating between posts in a topic buffer, copying
message bodies, storing Org links for selected commits, tracking new
repositories in the Forge database, and keeping notification read
status in sync between Emacs and GitHub via the REST API
(@ref{Notification and read-status synchronization}).

@item
@strong{GitHub Projects v2 integration.}  A suite of commands that interact
with the GitHub GraphQL API through the @samp{gh} command-line tool,
allowing you to set project status and estimates, list project items in
board order, discover field and option Node IDs, and insert Markdown
links to issues---all without leaving Emacs (@ref{GitHub Project integration}).
@end itemize

The package requires @samp{forge} (version 0.3.1 or later) and @samp{shut-up}.
The GitHub Project features additionally require the @samp{gh} CLI to be
installed and authenticated.

@node User options
@chapter User options

All user options belong to the @code{forge-extras} customization group.  Most
of them configure the GitHub Projects v2 integration; see
@ref{Setting up GitHub Project integration} for a
guided walkthrough.

@menu
