@end menu

@node Project owner and number
@section Project owner and number

@vindex forge-extras-project-owner
@vindex forge-extras-project-number
The user option @code{forge-extras-project-owner} specifies the GitHub owner
(organization or user name) that owns the target project.  Its type is a
string and its default value is @code{nil}.

The user option @code{forge-extras-project-number} specifies the project
number (the integer visible in the project's URL).  Its type is an
integer and its default value is @code{nil}.

These two options are used by @code{forge-extras-gh-get-issue-fields} to
construct the GraphQL query that retrieves project data for a given
issue.  You must set both before using any of the project-related
commands (@ref{GitHub Project integration}).

@node Project Node ID
@section Project Node ID

@vindex forge-extras-project-node-id
The user option @code{forge-extras-project-node-id} holds the global Relay
Node ID of the target GitHub Project.  Its type is a string and its
default value is @code{nil}.

This is the primary identifier used by most project commands.  See
@ref{Setting up GitHub Project integration} for
instructions on how to obtain it.

@node Status field Node ID
@section Status field Node ID

@vindex forge-extras-status-field-node-id
The user option @code{forge-extras-status-field-node-id} stores the global
Relay Node ID of the ``Status'' single-select field in the target project.
Its type is a string and its default value is @code{nil}.

This ID is required by @code{forge-extras-set-project-status}
(@ref{Setting project status}) and by the discovery
commands that inspect status options (@ref{Discovering project IDs}).
Use @code{forge-extras-get-project-field-ids} to find the correct value
(@ref{Getting project field IDs}).

@node Estimate field Node ID
@section Estimate field Node ID

@vindex forge-extras-estimate-field-node-id
The user option @code{forge-extras-estimate-field-node-id} stores the global
Relay Node ID of the ``Estimate'' numeric field in the target project.
Its type is a string and its default value is @code{nil}.

This ID is required by @code{forge-extras-set-project-estimate}
(@ref{Setting project estimates}).  Use
@code{forge-extras-get-project-field-ids} to find the correct value
(@ref{Getting project field IDs}).

@node Status option IDs alist
@section Status option IDs alist

@vindex forge-extras-status-option-ids-alist
The user option @code{forge-extras-status-option-ids-alist} maps
human-readable status names (such as ``Todo'', ``In Progress'', ``Done'') to
their corresponding GraphQL Option IDs for the ``Status'' single-select
field.  Its type is an alist mapping strings to strings, and its default
value is @code{nil}.

When @code{forge-extras-set-project-status} prompts you for a status, the
completion candidates come from the keys of this alist.  You can
populate it manually or use the output of
@code{forge-extras-discover-project-status-options}
(@ref{Discovering status options}), which
formats the data for easy insertion into your configuration.

@node Issue link state
@section Issue link state

@vindex forge-extras-issue-link-state
The user option @code{forge-extras-issue-link-state} controls which issues
@code{forge-extras-insert-issue-markdown-link} retrieves from GitHub.  Its
type is a choice among the strings @code{"open"}, @code{"closed"}, and @code{"all"}.
The default value is @code{"open"}.

If you frequently need to reference closed issues, change this to
@code{"all"}.  The value is passed directly to @samp{gh issue list --state}.

@node Debug flag
@section Debug flag

@vindex forge-extras-debug
The variable @code{forge-extras-debug}, when set to a non-nil value, enables
verbose debugging messages throughout @samp{forge-extras.el}.  These messages
are emitted via @code{forge-extras-message-debug} and appear in the
@samp{*Messages*} buffer.  The default value is @code{nil}.

This is a plain @code{defvar}, not a @code{defcustom}, so set it in your
configuration or toggle it interactively with @samp{M-: (setq
forge-extras-debug t)}.  It is useful for diagnosing failures in the
GraphQL API calls used by the project integration features
(@ref{GitHub Project integration}).

