@node Getting project field IDs
@subsection Getting project field IDs

@findex forge-extras-get-project-field-ids
The command @code{forge-extras-get-project-field-ids} queries the GitHub
GraphQL API for all fields defined in the project identified by
@code{forge-extras-project-node-id} and displays their names and Node IDs in
a formatted buffer named @samp{*GitHub Project Fields*}.

This is the primary tool for populating
@code{forge-extras-status-field-node-id}
(@ref{Status field Node ID}) and
@code{forge-extras-estimate-field-node-id}
(@ref{Estimate field Node ID}).

@node Discovering status options
@subsection Discovering status options

@findex forge-extras-discover-project-status-options
The command @code{forge-extras-discover-project-status-options} fetches all
available option names and Node IDs for the ``Status'' single-select field
configured via @code{forge-extras-status-field-node-id}.  The results are
displayed in a @samp{*GitHub Project Status Options*} buffer, formatted as an
alist that you can copy directly into your configuration for
@code{forge-extras-status-option-ids-alist}
(@ref{Status option IDs alist}).

Both @code{forge-extras-project-node-id} and @code{forge-extras-status-field-node-id}
must be set before running this command.

@node Looking up a single status option ID
@subsection Looking up a single status option ID

@findex forge-extras-get-project-status-option-id
If you already know the name of a status option (for example, ``Waiting'')
and need its Node ID, the command
@code{forge-extras-get-project-status-option-id} provides a shortcut.  It
prompts for the status name, fetches all options for the configured
status field, and displays the matching Option ID in the echo area.  The
search is case-insensitive.

If no match is found, the error message lists all available option names
so you can correct a typo.

@node Listing project items
@section Listing project items

