@node Repository tracking
@section Repository tracking

@findex forge-extras-track-repo-all-topics
The function @code{forge-extras-track-repo-all-topics} is the workhorse
behind @code{forge-extras-track-repository}
(@ref{Tracking repositories}).  It accepts a URL or
local path, resolves it to a repository, inserts it into the Forge
database, and pulls all topics.  You can call it directly when you have a
URL rather than a local directory.

@node GraphQL API functions
@section GraphQL API functions

@findex forge-extras-gh-get-issue-fields
@findex forge-extras-gh-parse-issue-fields
@findex forge-extras-gh-get-project-fields
@findex forge-extras-gh-parse-project-fields
@findex forge-extras-gh-add-issue-to-project
@findex forge-extras-gh-update-project-item-status-field
@findex forge-extras-gh-update-project-item-estimate-field
The GitHub Project integration is built on several public functions that
wrap the GraphQL API@.  These can be useful if you want to build custom
workflows:

@itemize
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-get-issue-fields} fetches raw project field data for
a given ISSUE-NUMBER and REPO-NAME@.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-parse-issue-fields} parses that raw data into a
property list with keys like @code{:issue-node-id}, @code{:status}, @code{:effort},
@code{:project-item-id}, and more.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-get-project-fields} fetches all field definitions for
a given PROJECT-NODE-ID@.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-parse-project-fields} parses the result into a list
of @samp{(NAME . ID)} cons cells.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-add-issue-to-project} adds an issue to a project and
returns the new project item Node ID@.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-update-project-item-status-field} updates a
single-select field (typically ``Status'') on a project item.
@item
@code{forge-extras-gh-update-project-item-estimate-field} updates a numeric
field (typically ``Estimate'') on a project item.
@end itemize

